[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man dies after being hit by lorry on A500 at Weston

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man was killed when he was struck by a lorry on the A500 south of Crewe.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The accident happened near Weston at about 21:30 BST on Tuesday.
West Midlands Ambulance Service joined colleagues from North West Ambulance Service after being called to the scene by Staffordshire Police.
The victim, a 20-year-old man who is said to be local and has not been named, was pronounced dead at the scene. The lorry driver was treated for shock.
